cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing the network of users who promote child unsafe content on YouTube.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper uses Convolutional Neural Networks to analyze video frames for detecting child unsafe content.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper uses supervised classification to detect child unsafe content based on various features.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper deals with analyzing comments on YouTube videos.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still relevant as the paper deals with detecting and characterizing malicious content on YouTube.
